## When to Use Context7 Tools

Automatically activate Context7 for:

### Documentation Needs

- **Library questions**: "How do I use [library]?"
- **Framework documentation**: "Show me [framework] docs for [feature]"
- **API references**: "What methods does [library] provide?"
- **Version-specific docs**: "[Library] v[X] documentation"

### Tool Workflow

**Always use this two-step process:**

1. **`resolve-library-id`** - First step for any library lookup:
   - Converts natural language to Context7 ID
   - Returns available versions
   - Shows documentation coverage
   - Provides trust score

2. **`get-library-docs`** - Retrieve actual documentation:
   - Uses ID from resolve-library-id
   - Can focus on specific topics
   - Returns contextualized docs
   - Optimized for AI consumption

### Supported Libraries

Context7 excels with popular frameworks and libraries:

- Next.js (`/vercel/next.js`)
- MongoDB (`/mongodb/docs`)
- Supabase (`/supabase/supabase`)
- And many more...

## Concrete Trigger Examples

User asks: "How do I use React hooks?"
→ Use: `resolve-library-id("react")` → `get-library-docs("/facebook/react", topic="hooks")`

User asks: "Next.js 14 app router documentation"
→ Use: `resolve-library-id("next.js")` → `get-library-docs("/vercel/next.js/v14.x.x", topic="app router")`

User asks: "MongoDB aggregation pipeline"
→ Use: `resolve-library-id("mongodb")` → `get-library-docs("/mongodb/docs", topic="aggregation")`

## Parameters Guide

**resolve-library-id:**

- `libraryName`: Natural language name or package name

**get-library-docs:**

- `context7CompatibleLibraryID`: ID from resolve step
- `topic`: Optional focus area (improves relevance)
- `tokens`: Documentation amount (default: 10000)

